Nevada: Paid QHPs up 2,100; Paid enrollments now at 71% of total
Wed, 02/26/2014 - 7:55pm
Nevada's latest update as of 2/22: Paid QHPs have shot up 2,095 from 17,047 to 19,142; unpaid QHPs are down702 to7,893 from 8,595, which means that Nevada, like Washington yesterday, is starting to convert unpaid enrollments to paid more quickly. Total enrollments are therefore up just 1,393.
Update as of 2/22: 27,035 consumers have confirmed QHP selections through Nevada Health Link, 19,142 have paid.
 Nevada Health Link (@NVHealthLink) February 26, 2014
